<% content_for :title, "License #{@version} — #{@kind.humanize} — Printwright" %>

<div class="container" style="max-width: 760px">
  <h1>Printwright license · <%= @kind.humanize %> · <%= @version %></h1>

  <p class="t-small muted">
    Canonical text. Certificates anchor its hash on Hedera as
    <code class="mono"><%= @hash %></code> — recompute it yourself:
  </p>
  <pre class="mono t-small" style="overflow-x:auto">curl -s <%= license_document_url(version: @version, kind: @kind, format: :txt) %> | sha256sum</pre>

  <p class="t-small">
    <%= link_to "Machine-readable permissions (JSON)",
      license_document_path(version: @version, kind: @kind, format: :json) %>
    are a convenience interpretation of the prose below. The prose and its anchored hash govern.
  </p>

  <pre style="white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: var(--s-4)"><%= @text %></pre>

  <p class="t-caption muted">
    Published versions are immutable — a changed text is a new version with a
    new hash. Certificates minted before this version anchored the hash of the
    offer's then-current terms; the anchored hash is always the contract.
  </p>
</div>
